cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with comparing ConvNets with multi-unit macaque IT cortex recordings. It may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category as it assesses the impact of depth and regularization techniques on representational similarity. Additionally, it could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it involves training and testing ConvNets. The paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with comparing machine learning models with biological visual systems. Lastly, it may belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category as it involves assessing representational similarity.
